----field----
field: {5A5684BB-8B54-44F6-ABCC-2BADA05ADA5D}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 1157

<p>This "How To" section contains a wide variety of Sitecore concepts and customizations, from the simple (<a href="~/link.aspx?_id=1F8E34AAE8F945739C9D9FDDA999C433&amp;_z=z">Create a simple XSL rendering</a>) to the complex (<a href="~/link.aspx?_id=C034AE92C4734E2191DA21C1EC643548&amp;_z=z">Create an HTTP Request Pipeline Processor</a>).</p>
<p>Sitecore is architected in such a way that complex system customizations are easily enabled through many hooks such as pipelines, insert rules, workflow, and user interface hooks such as validators, "gutter" status indicators and commands.</p>
<p>This section will cover a few of those topics, giving you a good background for tackling many of the other customization types which use many of the same principles.</p>
<p>In general, the <a href="~/link.aspx?_id=A9A2F7FAB1BB4F15B694241340D7D997&amp;_z=z">Topics </a>section is devoted to concepts, whereas this How To section is devoted to actual code and implementation. The majority of the examples are designed to be completed after you complete the <a href="~/link.aspx?_id=33E64068DFB742BAA262272103A007B2&amp;_z=z">Build My First Site</a> exercises.</p>
